  <p> Originally from Italy, where programming is a rather uncommon thing to do.
        Before Bootcamp, I only knew some HTML5, which I used to create my first web page, where I posted some of the photos I took with my Canon.
      I remember staying up all night twice in a row, trying to figure out how to create this web page - I loved it,
      I loved the fact that I had the tools to create absolutely anything from nothing at all.
      I felt powerful. I guess that's how it started.
  I have tried to learn how to use Blender and how to program in C++ in the past as well, as I'm interested in creating video games.
As of now, I would like to become an ethical hacker, but I'd also like to be able to create my own apps and much more.</p>
