 <tr>
  <td class="infotd">
    <h3>Bootcamp 2020: Spinning Wheel</h3>
    <p>
	My first programming project, concluding the 2 week Programming Bootcamp at
	City (2020). This Processing project was created with the use of conditionals, loops, randomness, interaction and animation of images.
  It consists of a spinning wheel divided into four sections, each with a set 'condition' on it.
  Depending on which condition the arrow stops on when the user clicks on it,
  the screen turns black and a quote appears.
  I also inserted a sequence of animated triangles at the top of the screen, as a sort of decoration. <a href="https://github.com/silviamazzantini/adby810">Check out the code on Github!</a>
    </p>
